This photo released Tuesday by the Peruvian Ministry of Culture shows an expert working on a wall decorated in high relief with the figure of a humanized toad from 3,800 years ago at Vichama archaeological site. The toad extending its arms over a human head would represent the announcement of the arrival of water after a drought, according to archaeologist Ruth Shady. Photo: VCGÂ  
